George Jacob Gershwin rwn born Jacob Bruskin Gershowitz September 1898 July 1937 was American composer and pianist whose compositions spanned both popular and classical genres Among his bestknown works are the orchestral compositions Rhapsody Blue 1924 and American Paris the songs Swanee 1919 and Fascinating Rhythm 1924 the jazz standard Got Rhythm 1930 and the opera Porgy and Bess 1935 which spawned the hit Summertime Gershwin studied piano under Charles Hambitzer and composition with Rubin Goldmark Henry Cowell and Joseph Brody began his career song plugger but soon started composing Broadway theater works with his brother Ira Gershwin and Buddy DeSylva moved Paris intending study with Nadia Boulanger but she refused him subsequently composed American Paris then returned New York City and wrote Porgy and Bess with Ira and DuBose Heyward was initially commercial failure but came considered one the most important American operas the twentieth century and American cultural classic Gershwin moved Hollywood and composed numerous film scores until his death 1937 from malignant brain tumor His compositions have been adapted for use films and television and several became jazz standards recorded and covered many variations Gershwin was Russian Jewish and Lithuanian Jewish ancestry His grandfather Jakov Gershowitz had served for years mechanic for the Imperial Russian Army earn the right free travel and residence Jew finally retiring near Saint Petersburg His teenage son Moishe Gershowitz worked leather cutter for womens shoes Moishe Gershowitz met and fell love with Roza Bruskina the teenage daughter furrier Vilnius She and her family moved New York due increasing antiJewish sentiment Russia changing her first name Rose Moishe faced with compulsory military service remained Russia moved America soon could afford Once New York changed his first name Morris Gershowitz lived with maternal uncle Brooklyn working foreman womens shoe factory married Rose July 1895 and Gershowitz soon Americanized his name GershwineTheir first child Ira Gershwin was born December 1896 after which the family moved into secondfloor apartment Brooklyns Snediker Avenue September 1898 George was born second son Morris and Rose Bruskin Gershwine their secondfloor apartment Brooklyns Snediker Avenue His birth certificate identifies him Jacob Gershwine with the surname pronounced Gershvin the Russian and Yiddish immigrant community had just one given name contrary the American practice giving children both first and middle name was named after his grandfather one time Russian army mechanic soon became known George and changed the spelling his surname Gershwin about the time became professional musician other family members followed suit After Ira and George another boy Arthur Gershwin 19001981 and girl Frances Gershwin 19061999 were born into the family The family lived many different residences their father changed dwellings with each new enterprise which became involved Mostly they grew around the Yiddish Theater District George and Ira frequented the local Yiddish theaters with George occasionally appearing onstage extra George lived usual childhood existence for children New York tenements running around with his boyhood friends roller skating and misbehaving the streets Until 1908 cared nothing for music when tenyearold was intrigued upon hearing his friend Maxie Rosenzweigs violin recital The sound and the way his friend played captured him around the same time Georges parents had bought piano for lessons for his older brother Ira but his parents surprise and Iras relief was George who spent more time playing Although his younger sister Frances was the first the family make living through her musical talents she married young and devoted herself being mother and housewife thus surrendering any serious time musical endeavors Having given her performing career she settled upon painting creative outlet which had also been hobby George briefly pursued Arthur Gershwin followed the paths George and Ira also becoming composer songs musicals and short piano works With degree frustration George tried various piano teachers for some two years circa 1911 before finally being introduced Charles Hambitzer Jack Miller circa 1913 the pianist the Beethoven Symphony Orchestra Until his death 1918 Hambitzer remained Gershwins musical mentor and taught him conventional piano technique introduced him music the European classical tradition and encouraged him attend orchestral concerts Following such concerts young Gershwin would essentially try play the piano home the music had heard from recall and without sheet musiccitation needed matter course Gershwin later studied with the classical composer Rubin Goldmark and avantgarde composertheorist Henry Cowell thus formalizing his classical music trainingcitation needed 1913 Gershwin left school the age and found his first job song plugger His employer was Jerome Remick and Company Detroitbased publishing firm with branch office New York Citys Tin Pan Alley and earned week His first published song was When You Want You Cant Get When Youve Got You Dont Want 1916 when Gershwin was only years old earned him cents 1916 Gershwin started working for Aeolian Company and Standard Music Rolls New York recording and arranging produced dozens not hundreds rolls under his own and assumed names pseudonyms attributed Gershwin include Fred Murtha and Bert Wynn also recorded rolls his own compositions for the DuoArt and WelteMignon reproducing pianos well recording piano rolls Gershwin made brief foray into vaudeville accompanying both Nora Bayes and Louise Dresser the piano His 1917 novelty ragtime Rialto Ripples was commercial success 1919 scored his first big national hit with his song Swanee with words Irving Caesar Jolson famous Broadway singer the day heard Gershwin perform Swanee party and decided sing one his shows the late 1910s Gershwin met songwriter and music director William Daly The two collaborated the Broadway musicals Piccadilly Broadway 1920 and For Goodness Sake 1922 and jointly composed the score for Our Nell 1923 This was the beginning long friendship Daly was frequent arranger orchestrator and conductor Gershwins music and Gershwin periodically turned him for musical advice 1924 Gershwin composed his first major classical work Rhapsody Blue for orchestra and piano was orchestrated Ferde Grof and premiered Paul Whitemans Concert Band New York subsequently went his most popular work and established Gershwins signature style and genius blending vastly different musical styles revolutionary ways Since the early 1920s Gershwin frequently worked with the lyricist Buddy DeSylva Together they created the experimental oneact jazz opera Blue Monday set Harlem widely regarded forerunner the groundbreaking Porgy and Bess 1924 George and Ira Gershwin collaborated stage musical comedy Lady Good which included such future standards Fascinating Rhythm and Lady Good They followed this with Kay 1926 Funny Face 1927 and Strike the Band 1927 and 1930 Gershwin allowed the song with modified title UCLA used football fight song Strike The Band for UCLA the mid1920s Gershwin stayed Paris for short period time during which applied study composition with the noted Nadia Boulanger who along with several other prospective tutors such Maurice Ravel rejected him They were afraid that rigorous classical study would ruin his jazzinfluenced style Maurice Ravels rejection letter Gershwin told him Why become secondrate Ravel when youre already firstrate Gershwin While there Gershwin wrote American Paris This work received mixed reviews upon its first performance Carnegie Hall December 1928 but quickly became part the standard repertoire Europe and the United States Growing tired the Parisian musical scene Gershwin returned the United Statescitation needed 1929 Gershwin was contracted Fox Film Corporation compose the score for the movie Delicious Only two pieces were used the final f